# PowerShell → C# Conversion Mapping Rules

These rules govern how the Cursor Agent CLI cleanup pass transforms mechanically converted C# code into idiomatic, compilable .NET 10 code.

## Module and Logging Mappings

| PowerShell | C# Replacement |
|---|---|
| `Import-Module GlobalFunctions -Force` | Remove; use NLog via DI or `LogManager.GetCurrentClassLogger()` |
| `Write-LogMessage "X" -Level INFO` | `_logger.Info("X")` |
| `Write-LogMessage "X" -Level WARN` | `_logger.Warn("X")` |
| `Write-LogMessage "X" -Level ERROR` | `_logger.Error("X")` |
| `Write-LogMessage "X" -Level DEBUG` | `_logger.Debug("X")` |
| `Write-Host "X"` | `Console.WriteLine("X")` or `_logger.Info("X")` depending on context |
| `Write-Output "X"` | `Console.WriteLine("X")` for pipeline-less scripts; return value for functions |
| `Write-Warning "X"` | `_logger.Warn("X")` |
| `Write-Error "X"` | `_logger.Error("X")` or `throw new InvalidOperationException("X")` |
| `Send-Sms -Receiver $num -Message $msg` | `await _smsService.SendAsync(number, message)` with `ISmsService` interface |

## File and IO Mappings

| PowerShell | C# Replacement |
|---|---|
| `Get-Content -LiteralPath $p -Raw` | `await File.ReadAllTextAsync(path, Encoding.UTF8)` |
| `Get-Content -LiteralPath $p -Raw -Encoding UTF8` | `await File.ReadAllTextAsync(path, Encoding.UTF8)` |
| `Set-Content -LiteralPath $p -Value $v` | `await File.WriteAllTextAsync(path, value, Encoding.UTF8)` |
| `Get-Content ... \| ConvertFrom-Json` | `JsonSerializer.Deserialize<T>(json, jsonOptions)` |
| `ConvertTo-Json -Depth N` | `JsonSerializer.Serialize(obj, jsonOptions)` with `WriteIndented = true` |
| `Test-Path -LiteralPath $p` | `File.Exists(path)` or `Directory.Exists(path)` |
| `New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $p -Force` | `Directory.CreateDirectory(path)` |
| `Get-ChildItem -LiteralPath $p -Recurse -File` | `Directory.EnumerateFiles(path, "*", SearchOption.AllDirectories)` |
| `Get-ChildItem -LiteralPath $p -Directory` | `Directory.EnumerateDirectories(path)` |
| `Remove-Item -LiteralPath $p -Force` | `File.Delete(path)` or `Directory.Delete(path, recursive)` |
| `Join-Path $a $b` | `Path.Combine(a, b)` |
| `Split-Path $p -Parent` | `Path.GetDirectoryName(path)` |
| `Split-Path $p -Leaf` | `Path.GetFileName(path)` |
| `Resolve-Path -LiteralPath $p` | `Path.GetFullPath(path)` |

## JSON Options Standard

```csharp
private static readonly JsonSerializerOptions JsonOptions = new()
{
    WriteIndented = true,
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase,
    DefaultIgnoreCondition = JsonIgnoreCondition.WhenWritingNull,
    Encoder = System.Text.Encodings.Web.JavaScriptEncoder.UnsafeRelaxedJsonEscaping
};
```

## HTTP and REST Mappings

| PowerShell | C# Replacement |
|---|---|
| `Invoke-RestMethod -Uri $url -Method Get` | `await _httpClient.GetFromJsonAsync<T>(url)` |
| `Invoke-RestMethod -Uri $url -Method Post -Body $b -ContentType 'application/json'` | `await _httpClient.PostAsJsonAsync(url, body)` |
| `Invoke-WebRequest -Uri $url ...` | `await _httpClient.SendAsync(request)` for full control |
| `$resp.Content \| ConvertFrom-Json` | Response is already deserialized with `GetFromJsonAsync<T>` |

Use `IHttpClientFactory` via DI. Named clients for different base URLs.

## Process Execution Mappings

| PowerShell | C# Replacement |
|---|---|
| `& pwsh.exe @args` | `Process.Start(psi)` with `ProcessStartInfo` |
| `Start-Process -FilePath $exe -ArgumentList $args -Wait` | `process.WaitForExitAsync()` |
| `$LASTEXITCODE` | `process.ExitCode` |

## Data Structure Mappings

| PowerShell | C# Replacement |
|---|---|
| `@{}` (hashtable) | `Dictionary<string, object>` or typed class |
| `[ordered]@{}` | `Dictionary<string, object>` preserving insertion order, or typed record |
| `[System.Collections.ArrayList]::new()` | `List<T>` with concrete type |
| `[System.Collections.Generic.HashSet[string]]::new()` | `HashSet<string>(StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase)` |
| `[PSCustomObject]@{ Key = Value }` | Typed class or anonymous object |
| `$array += $item` | `list.Add(item)` — never use array concatenation in C# |

## Control Flow Mappings

| PowerShell | C# Replacement |
|---|---|
| `foreach ($item in $collection)` | `foreach (var item in collection)` |
| `$collection \| ForEach-Object { ... }` | `collection.Select(x => ...).ToList()` or `foreach` |
| `$collection \| Where-Object { ... }` | `collection.Where(x => ...).ToList()` |
| `$collection \| Sort-Object Property` | `collection.OrderBy(x => x.Property).ToList()` |
| `$collection \| Select-Object -First N` | `collection.Take(n)` |
| `$collection \| Group-Object Property` | `collection.GroupBy(x => x.Property)` |
| `$collection \| Measure-Object -Sum` | `collection.Sum(x => x.Value)` |
| `try { ... } catch { Write-Warning $_.Exception.Message }` | `try { ... } catch (Exception ex) { _logger.Warn(ex.Message); }` |
| `$ErrorActionPreference = 'Stop'` | Remove; C# throws by default |

## String Mappings

| PowerShell | C# Replacement |
|---|---|
| `"Hello $($variable)"` | `$"Hello {variable}"` |
| `$str -match 'pattern'` | `Regex.IsMatch(str, "pattern")` |
| `$str -replace 'old','new'` | `Regex.Replace(str, "old", "new")` |
| `$str -split ','` | `str.Split(',')` |
| `$str.Trim()` | `str?.Trim()` (null-safe) |
| `[string]::IsNullOrWhiteSpace($s)` | `string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(s)` |

## Encoding

| PowerShell | C# Replacement |
|---|---|
| `-Encoding UTF8` | `Encoding.UTF8` |
| `-Encoding windows-1252` / `cp1252` | `Encoding.GetEncoding(1252)` (register with `Encoding.RegisterProvider(CodePagesEncodingProvider.Instance)`) |

## Parameter to Property Mapping

PowerShell `param()` blocks become constructor parameters or configuration classes:

```csharp
// PowerShell:
// param([string]$SourceRoot = 'C:\opt\data', [int]$MaxIterations = 5)

public class AnalysisOptions
{
    public string SourceRoot { get; set; } = @"C:\opt\data";
    public int MaxIterations { get; set; } = 5;
}
```

Bind from `appsettings.json` via `IOptions<AnalysisOptions>`.

## Script-Level Variables

PowerShell `$script:variable` becomes private class fields:

```csharp
// PowerShell: $script:cache = @{}
private readonly Dictionary<string, object> _cache = new();
```

## Required Using Statements

Every converted file should include at minimum:

```csharp
using System.Text;
using System.Text.Json;
using System.Text.Json.Serialization;
using System.Text.RegularExpressions;
using NLog;
```

## .csproj Package References

Generated projects must include:

```xml
<PackageReference Include="NLog" Version="5.*" />
<PackageReference Include="NLog.Extensions.Logging" Version="5.*" />
<PackageReference Include="System.Text.Encoding.CodePages" Version="9.*" />
```
